name: Seabiscuit
short_description:
The Seabiscuit codebase has been merged with https://sourceforge.net/projects/fh-miscellany

Seabiscuit is a tiny, proof-of-concept-ish Web browser made for fun. It is coded in Python 3, PyQt4, HTML, and JavaScript, and released under the MIT License. Seabiscuit is designed for Linux, but it might run on other Unix-like OSes such as FreeBSD. To run it, you will need Python 3, PyQt4, and a reasonably-common terminal emulator.

The Seabiscuit source code is hosted in a Git repository. You can get it by running:
git clone git://git.code.sf.net/p/biscuit-browser/code biscuit-browser-code

README: https://sourceforge.net/p/biscuit-browser/wiki/Readme/
LICENSING: https://sourceforge.net/p/biscuit-browser/wiki/Licensing/
summary: Unorthodox Linux Web browser coded for fun
